This paper discusses the formalization of the concept of agents in multivariate Markov chains, which involves machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the goal-directed behavior of agents, which is a common topic in systems and control (cs.SY) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
